title: John Rowe's college football picks for Oct. 10 - Football
text:
Rowe's picks 
Navy (+14) against *Notre Dame — Have to be concerned about the Irish state of mind after their loss to Clemson. They could get caught looking ahead to USC.
*Alabama (-16) over Arkansas — As good as Arkansas' running game is, Alabama's run defense is even better.
*Michigan (7 1/2) over Northwestern — The Wolverines have another chance to prove they're better than everybody thought.
Play of the day 
*Utah (-7) over California — A so-so schedule finally catches up to Cal. Utah is fresh after its bye week.
Other games 
*Kansas State (+10) against TCU; *Missouri (+4) against Florida; *West Virginia (-6 1/2) over Oklahoma State; *LSU (-20) over South Carolina
*home games
Last week: 2-5-1; Season: 13-26-1; Plays of the day: 1-4
